  "description": [
    "VOL LXXVII No 11 NEWS IN BRIEF RESIDENTS PROTEST The Center School PTA is prepared to vociferate over the taking of 75 feet from play ground land at the Center School The Board of Educa tion has voted to abandon the land to the town for sale to developers of an adjacent Main Street block The PTA has called for lOOo turnout at the Town Council meeting Tuesday night to complain i They have previously been ex cited over losing Center Play ground to the State Highway Department It is just a shame that our world is turn ing into just supermarkets and parking lots says a PTA representative They say they will fight to the end PARKS NAMED Two East Hartford Parks will bear the names of two respected former residents of the town The 55 acre South End Park has been designated by the Park Board henceforth as Dr Richard J Gorman Park in honor of the former president of the State Board of Veterinary Reg istration and Examination The North End Park has re ceived the name Cornelius G McAuliffe Park in memory of the towns former Superin tendent of Welfare Dr Gor man died March 28"
  ],
